Presumably, tortoise activity corresponds with monsoonal rains and vegetation growth (
Bury et al. 2002
). 
Goode's
Thornscrub Tortoise is active from at least June well into November; we lack data on activity during the dry season. In Sonora, the TDF hugs the western edge of the Sierra Madre Occidental and the biome hosts extremely lush vegetation during periods of summer rainfall (
July-September
). During dry periods, the TDF is almost entirely leafless, but with many spectacularly blooming trees and large columnar cacti (
Krizman 1972
; 
Van Devender et al. 2000
).
